  "title": "Recruitment Consultant, Built-Environment",
  "description": "<p>The consulting role represents a face of our Practice via a 360-recruitment cycle, to develop our Urban Markets for the Built Environment across the Construction Desk</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Business Development: Cold-calling, Telemarketing &amp; Networking and through the maintaining of excellent relationships with the Clients of the targeted market.</li>\n  <li>Technical Search: Utilitize a variety of methods to develop candidate pipeline, forming a comprehensive network of key-talents that are both passive and active across the allocated desk (Construction and Design)</li>\n  <li>Market Specialization: Be on top of industry trends, being alert to project, plans and movements of candidates; providing periodical updates and outlooks</li>\n  <li>Sales Management: Exceeding set sales-target on a Quarterly and Annual basis</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The role is on a full-commissioned basis (60% of Sales)</strong>; please only apply if you are open to the arrangement and are willing to find out further.</p>\n<p>If the role resonates with you and your professional experience complements the responsibilities listed, send your resume to <strong>dickson@bayesrecruitment.com.sg</strong></p>\n<p>Dickson KOH, Managing Partner<br>\nbayesrecruitment.com</p>",
